  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. Evidence confidence is approximately 50% due to limited sample size (N=11), single test condition, and moderate material-property uncertainty; these limitations are documented honestly throughout. Despite wide uncertainty bounds, the model ensemble achieves all required credibility levels and the E/uval metric remains below 1.96 for all QoIs. The assessment team accepts the residual uncertainty as consistent with a Medium model-risk, Medium decision-consequence COU and records a clear rationale. No weakener is present; this is a structurally clean package.",
